Um, no.<br>
<br>
The point is that the mob in question is either the most difficult, or second most difficult encounter in the game. <br>
<br>
One guild has killed the Emperor. One guild has killed Seru. <br>
<br>
To do those encounters the guilds in question had to spend massive amounts of time preparing the guild to get into their chambers, be equipped with special weapons that can actually do damage, etc.<br>
<br>
That amount of effort should be rewarded with items that everyone who committed their time to beating the encounter would want. Not "I guess I'll take it if it's going to rot" or "I guess I'll take it if it doesn't cost points".<br>
<br>
Sure, there's something to be said for saying that the victory is part of the reward. Any guild who tries these encounters is obviously motivated by that. But the tangible benefit should be commensurate with the difficulty of the encounter, with the amount of time invested, and with the sense of accomplishment you experience once you've won.<br>
<br>
This item doesn't meet those criteria.<br>
